*** ****** *** ** ******** *** ** *** **** ******** **** **** **** **** having been a dental patient all my life, you can really take my word for it. He gets patients from many different parts of the country, as well as overseas, especially critical cases, or situations where all other dentists have given up. Extremely brilliant with his work, which looks almost effortless thanks to his many many years of practice, it is admirable how he and his equally dedicated and friendly, and above all well skilled team work. The most important thing any patient would want is not to be treated as 'just another patient', but as a human being with real questions, concerns and apprehensions, and Dr. Girish Rao and his team know exactly how to put you at ease and help you focus on just getting better! Not to mention, the quality of work is par excellence, and pre and post care attention, impeccable. The moment I entered their clinic, I just felt rest assured that even my critical case will turn out fine. I do consider myself extremely lucky to have found such a wonderful doctor here in Bangalore. My writeup I'm sure is indicative not only of the value Dr. Girish and his team add to your treatment and recovery, but also the very genuine, human care you'll get. If you, like me, have been disappointed with other short-sighted dentists before, meeting Dr.Rao will give you hope - and prove that good doctors still exist. And he and his family, and the team also do a lot of good work even outside of this actively running practice. I'm so inspired, and feel sincere sense of gratitude to have known, above all a dedicated family of doctors who care! Heartfully recommended!

Dr. Girish Rao is the most wonderful and refined doctor that I have ever known. It was unfortunate for my family to have my father contract oral cancer, but we were doubly fortunate to have come in contact with Dr. Girish. The sensitivity with which he broke out the news to us, to explaining about the disease and assuring us that he will remove the disease out of my dad's system, and that he shall be able get back to his routine life again, was more than we could ever ask for. Doing numerous rounds to the ward with his team, addressing dad's minutest concern, ensuring his overall well-being - I personally can't reciprocate in any way than to just bow down in utmost humility with folded hands and say 'thank you' for gifting another life to my dad and empowering me to create more beautiful memories with him. Every person from the staff to the doctor in Mukha clinic, is so humble and always smiling. This is possibly the only clinic I look forward to visiting again and again. They stand true to their motto of 3 E's - Educate, Empower and Enhance. Wish the tribe of such sincere and committed doctors keeps growing. Wish the best for my favourite doctor and my favourite clinic, Mukha. :)
